abstract: The S.E.C. also proposed new rules outlining the process for banks and other firms that trade derivatives to register with the agency.

keywords.name: subject
keywords.value: Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act (2010)

lead_paragraph: The Securities and Exchange Commission became the latest agency on Wednesday to support an initial version of the so-called Volcker Rule, a new regulation aimed at curtailing risky trading on Wall Street.
